brief_summary.textblock:
This study will assess an investigational medication for patients with chronic renal
      insufficiency (pre-dialysis) who have secondary hyperparathyroidism.

clinical_study.brief_title: Study for Secondary Hyperparathyroidism in Chronic Renal Insufficiency Patients

group.description: Cinacalcet administered orally once daily with dose titrated starting at 30 mg
group.title: Cinacalcet (AMG 073)

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients must have chronic renal insufficiency (pre-dialysis)

          -  Have below normal creatinine clearance

          -  Have elevated parathyroid hormone levels

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnant or nursing

          -  Heart attack in the last 3 months.

intervention.description: Initially receive 1 tablet of study medication (cinacalcet or placebo) once daily.  Possible sequential dose titrations are 30, 60, 90, 120, 180mg cinacalcet or placebo) daily.  The titration phase was 12 weeks and the efficacy assessment phase was 6 weeks.
